{
  "texts": [
    "There are a number of challenges that arise when we introduce public data into the private machine learning pipeline (H. Brown et al., 2022; Tramèr, Kamath, & Carlini, 2022).",
    "One difficulty involves the fact that publicly available data may not be appropriate to treat as fully 'public.'",
    "Some examples include when data is posted online illegally, without the original owner's knowledge or consent, or for use exclusively in one particular context; concerns of contextual integrity (Nissenbaum, 2004).",
    "It is a risk to consider models that treat such content as public.",
    "Another issue pertains to the actual utility of public data in models used for privacy-sensitive settings."
  ]
}